# Fixture for the `doge build` standalone-binary test (build_produces_standalone_binary
# in cli.rs). It has its own script — not hello.doge — because the build cache is
# keyed by source: another test builds hello.doge in parallel, and sharing a source
# would race two builds on the same cached binary. Its printed line is the test's
# expected stdout.
bark "much standalone. very wow."
wow
